## Lazy-loading rule

Open only the target of the matching row. Do not preload the corpus, `context/`,
or sibling rows "just in case". One row, one file.

## Regeneration recipe

Indexes are derived artifacts and are NOT committed: `llms.txt` and any RAG
index regenerate from source. The recipe (`scripts/reindex.py`) IS committed.
Rebuild with:

```
make reindex
```
